snippet: A spectacular failure to put a satellite into orbit raises the question, American officials said, of whether Kim Jong-un will attempt to recover by staging a larger provocation.
abstract: Spectacular failure of a $1 billion rocket meant to put a satellite into orbit is a public humiliation for North Korean leader Kim Jong-un, and may present the first test of whether anyone will dare to challenge his fledgling rule; American officials express worry that Kim may be tempted to recover by staging a larger provocation.

byline.original: By CHOE SANG-HUN and DAVID E. SANGER
byline.contributor: Choe Sang-hun reported from Seoul, and David E. Sanger from Cambridge, Mass. Rick Gladstone and William J. Broad contributed reporting from New York.

lead_paragraph: A spectacular failure to put a satellite into orbit raises the question, American officials said, of whether Kim Jong-un will attempt to recover by staging a larger provocation.

headline.seo: Failed North Korean Launching a Setback for Kim Jong-un
headline.main: Rocket Failure May Be Test of North Korean Leader’s Power
headline.print_headline: Rocket Failure May Test Leader of North Korea
